      "file_path": "runtime/pom.xml",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 166,
      "message": "Well you need to define where you push the jars when you use the deploy goal in maven.\nI had to define this at the very beginning of Onap, so it's a legacy. May be that is now automatically provided by the settings.xml of the LF jobs ? It does not appear in your policy parent neither in the oparent\n\nAnyway, we used to define a maximum of things in the Pom because we wanted the Build to be autonomous. You could/can do all admin operations without having to add anything in the settings.xml. That was easier for all the devs (new ones).\n\nOthers projects have that as well (SO , etc ...)",
